Important Hardware Details
Background Format

Mode 7 uses:

1 background layer

128×128 tile map

8×8 tiles

256 tiles available

This creates a 1024×1024 pixel texture plane.

Fixed-Point Math

The matrix values use:

16-bit signed fixed point

8.8 precision

Meaning:

1.0 = 256
0.5 = 128

This is important if you're implementing it in an emulator or FPGA.

Perspective Trick

Mode 7 itself does NOT do perspective.

Games fake perspective by:

Changing the matrix per scanline during horizontal blank (HDMA).

So each row of the screen uses a different scale.

Example:

top of screen → small scale
bottom of screen → large scale

Result:

   horizon
      |
      v
-------------------
\                 /
 \               /
  \             /
   \___________/

That’s why Mario Kart looks like a 3D road.

Hardware Limitation (Important for Your Console Design)

Mode 7 can only transform one background layer.

Sprites are rendered normally and placed on top.

This is why games:

render the road with Mode 7

render cars as sprites.

Why This Matters For Your Nitro-Core-DX

